DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Ciacco

who   : A Florentine remembered for his appetite.
what  : A soul prone in cold filthy rain, under the claws of Cerberus.
where : Circle III — Gluttony.
why   : He made a god of the belly.
when  : In the endless storm.
how   : He lifts his face from the mire only to prophesy Florence's coming grief.

